					Title: <b>Android client to bitcoind server ?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>azw409</b> on <b>August 26, 2013, 04:37:20 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">I run a bitcoind server but would like a client with a similar interface to bitcoin-qt on Android. Does such a thing exist ?<br /><br />Thanks<br /><br /></div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Android client to bitcoind server ?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>Remember remember the 5th of November</b> on <b>August 26, 2013, 08:46:05 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">If you want a full bitcoin node on Android, that will be tough, most Android clients are SPV clients or they don&#039;t store the entire blockchain.</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Android client to bitcoind server ?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>Mike Hearn</b> on <b>August 29, 2013, 01:23:17 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">If you run your own bitcoind you can just use Bitcoin Wallet and set your server as the trusted peer.</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: Android client to bitcoind server ?</b><br />
